1
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:35,301
[Classical music plays]

2
00:00:35,368 --> 00:00:37,461
Narrator; Christchurch...

3
00:00:37,537 --> 00:00:40,370
New Zealand's city
of the plains.

4
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:43,773
Here, when spring comes
to Canterbury,

5
00:00:43,843 --> 00:00:46,141
daffodils bloom gay
and golden

6
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:49,272
in the woodland
of Hagley Park.

7
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:50,748
Through the park,

8
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:54,514
tree-bordered, green-banked,
the Avon flows,

9
00:00:54,587 --> 00:00:57,249
a small and placid stream.

10
00:00:57,323 --> 00:00:59,985
The riverbank is cool
and green,

11
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,995
a quiet haven from the bustle
of the city.

12
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:04,894
[Trolley bell dings]

13
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:11,166
Nearby are tall buildings,

14
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:14,434
busy streets,
and the heart of the city,

15
00:01:14,507 --> 00:01:16,941
Cathedral Square.

16
00:01:17,010 --> 00:01:18,944
Every city street is flat,

17
00:01:19,012 --> 00:01:21,446
so there are bicycles
everywhere.

18
00:01:21,514 --> 00:01:23,607
This is a city of cycling.

19
00:01:23,683 --> 00:01:25,014
[Bell rings]

20
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:33,851
Mothers, fathers, sons,
and daughters all on wheels...

21
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:36,191
cyclists of all ages

22
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:40,426
from 8 to 80 ride to play
or work each day.

23
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,434
There are thousands of them,

24
00:01:42,502 --> 00:01:46,165
and only Copenhagen
is said to boast more bicycles.

25
00:01:49,242 --> 00:01:51,767
Canterbury University
College...

26
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:56,009
weathered gray stone buildings,
shadowed cloisters.

27
00:01:56,082 --> 00:01:58,983
It was here Lord Rutherford
began a great career.

28
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:03,455
The girls' high school stands
in Cranmer Square,

29
00:02:03,523 --> 00:02:07,653
and not far away are
the broad acres of Hagley Park,

30
00:02:07,727 --> 00:02:09,854
with playing fields
for many sports.

31
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:17,133
In spring, summer, and autumn,

32
00:02:17,203 --> 00:02:20,969
Christchurch gardens are gay
and colored.

33
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,907
Yes, Christchurch,

34
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:27,242
New Zealand's city
of the plains.

35
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:32,148
[Girls screaming]

36
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:40,859
[Panting, screaming]

37
00:02:40,927 --> 00:02:43,191
[Silence]

38
00:02:43,263 --> 00:02:44,890
[Screaming resumes]

39
00:02:44,964 --> 00:02:48,832
[Silence]

40
00:02:48,902 --> 00:02:51,894
[Screaming resumes]

41
00:02:53,806 --> 00:02:55,740
Mummy!

42
00:02:55,808 --> 00:02:57,275
Mummy!

43
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:00,604
Mummy!

44
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,614
[Screaming resumes]

45
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:12,884
[Screaming and sobbing]

46
00:03:12,959 --> 00:03:15,553
It's Mummy!

47
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:17,562
She's terribly hurt!

48
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,791
Please... help us!

49
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:30,469
[Piano introduction to "Just
a Closer Walk with Thee" plays]

50
